# Hourbour — Rules & Never-Again Patterns
LONG-TERM. Hourbour-specific only. System-wide rules → docs/memory/feedback.md
Schema: each rule must have [added: YYYY-MM-DD] · Rules without dates are invalid.
🔴 CRITICAL · 🟡 IMPORTANT · 🟢 GUIDANCE

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL

[added: 2026-03-26] Never use financial jargon: "leverage", "yield", "portfolio rebalancing" — plain English only
[added: 2026-03-26] Never sound like a bank, a finance professor, or a sales pitch — ever
[added: 2026-03-26] Copy tone: trustworthy, clear, approachable. One idea per sentence.

---

## 🟡 IMPORTANT

[added: 2026-03-26] Lena: plain English always. Short paragraphs. "Your money" not "one's finances".
[added: 2026-03-26] Rio: LinkedIn Ads primary. Exclude high-net-worth and wealth management interest segments.
[added: 2026-03-26] Felix: track expansion MRR and contraction MRR separately — not just net MRR
[added: 2026-03-26] Kai: watch for drop in session frequency per user — early churn signal, flag before MRR drops

---

## 🟢 GUIDANCE

[added: 2026-03-26] LinkedIn CTA: "Try Hourbour free" primary · "See the demo" secondary
[added: 2026-03-26] Content: helpful financial tips + product demos. Not salesy. Not preachy.
[added: 2026-03-26] Social proof content performs well — user outcomes, testimonials

---

## Never Again
No entries yet. Populated from Adjourning after any Hourbour error.